Tattoos hurt, so why do we continue to get them? 

Tattoos tell a story as old as time itself that we are not just physical creatures, animals that roam the Earth and submit to their instincts for survival that we are more . 

That we are spiritual beings, and we seek a spiritual food or truth something that fills our souls, with love, purpose, and gratitude. 
 
The same reason why we can obtain all the materials wealth and happiness, and still feel empty inside because we forget to feed our soul, with the infinite. 

truth be told that if we are not growing then we are dying. Which is why in the absence of problems people tend to create their own and sometimes they find it in a Tattoo.

I can always tell the difference between the person who is looking for a problem in a tattoo as opposed to looking for a tattoo for meaning. 
 
Which is my favorite kind of artwork to do? 
Those tattoos that remind you that even some of the lowest parts of your life you were able to overcome and prevail. 

And just as how you do, anything is how you do everything there is no pain that you can’t endure there is no there is no hurdle that you can’t mount there is no discipline that you can’t uphold there is no mountain you can’t climb and no person that you can’t reach no mindset that you can’t achieve

We are spiritual beings and in the artwork that surrounds us, and most importantly that we carry on our skin should be a constant reminder to feed our soul to grow to be better to be stronger to be wiser, to be more disciplined, to be more loving, to be more grateful.

 We are spiritual beings.

Does numbing cream actually work? 🧐

So everybody’s skin is different and pain tolerance is attached to that as well. 🤨

😋I go through a lot of clients and I can honestly say around 50% of people approve of numbing cream. 😋

while the other 50% say it had no significant difference what so ever. 🙃

I personally have tried out numbing cream with a lidocaine percentage of at least 8% 

and I can honestly say it didn’t take the pain away but that it took the edge ✋🤚 off. 

So should you 🫵 try out numbing cream for your next tattoo?

Couple years ago I told people that the numbing cream hype was completely overrated and that you’re probably wasting your time.

But today they have so many different options on the market a lot of which have really good reviews.🦻🦻

The problem in the past was that 90% of the numbing creams on the market, used the working agent lidocaine with a percentage under 4%🤏 that’s really small amount. 

Today brands like TKTX cell numbing cream with a lidocaine percentage of up to 12% and you can definitely tell the difference!! 🤌

So thankfully these numbing creams have also come down in price a lot and it wouldn’t hurt to give it a try. 😃

Especially if it makes your experience just a little bit better because you don’t have to worry about the pain as much as you would have. 😁
